The paper deals with instance segmentation, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed model is an end-to-end recurrent neural network (RNN) architecture with an attention mechanism, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The model is designed to produce detailed instance segmentations, which involves robotics (cs.RO) and natural language processing (cs.CL) for image captioning and visual question answering.
